üñ•Ô∏è 1. Output with echo
The echo command is used to display text or variable values.

Basic Example
echo "Hello, World!"

Print Variable
name="Rakesh"
echo "My name is $name"

Options:
-n ‚Üí No newline at the end
echo -n "Enter your name: "

-e ‚Üí Enable escape sequences
echo -e "Line1\nLine2"     # prints on two lines
echo -e "Hello\tWorld"     # adds a tab

‚å®Ô∏è 2. Input with read
The read command takes user input.

Basic Example
read name
echo "Hello, $name"

With Prompt
read -p "Enter your name: " name
echo "Welcome, $name!"

With Multiple Variables
read -p "Enter your first and last name: " first last
echo "First: $first, Last: $last"

With Silent Input (passwords)
read -sp "Enter your password: " password
echo
echo "Password entered (hidden): $password"

With Timeout
read -t 5 -p "Enter your name (within 5 sec): " name
echo "Name: $name"

